    "[25,26].Consider first the pressure profiles, drawn in Fig. 4A.",
    "Compared with the GPD model results [25,26], these profiles are more compact because the RL predictions for θ P q 1 fall faster with increasing.",
    "The qualitative features of the profiles in Fig. 4A suggest a physical interpretation.",
    "Namely, the meson pressures are positive and large on the neighbourhood r 0, whereupon the meson's dressed-valence constituents are pushing away from each other.",
    "With increasing separation, the pressure switches sign, indicating a transition to the domain wherewithin confinement forces exert their influence on the pair."
